      "date": "2016-02-01 13:22:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\nMinh, jenkins script should be fixed to accommodate to this changes. The name of TAR file is not correct that passed to lbuild:\n+ bash -x /var/lib/jenkins/workspace/lustre-reviews/arch/x86_64/build_type/server/distro/el7/ib_stack/inkernel/build/lbuild --kernelrpm=/var/lib/jenkins/workspace/../lbuild-data//kernelrpm --kerneltree=/var/lib/jenkins/workspace/../lbuild-data//kerneltree --reusebuild=/var/lib/jenkins/workspace/../lbuild-data//reusebuild --ccache --lustre=/var/lib/jenkins/workspace/lustre-reviews/arch/x86_64/build_type/server/distro/el7/ib_stack/inkernel/lustre-.tar.gz --target=3.10-rhel7 --distro=rhel7.1 --ofed-version=inkernel",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "a505de7791179b788492254a888e8c4a3e3415ca",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2016-02-02 00:03:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nIt is a bad idea to replace LUSTRE_VERSION used for the module version string with something generic like VERSION. That will be disliked by the upstream folks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
